               <p>(The case opened by Mr. Schoen.)</p>
               <p>- CHAPMAN sworn.</p>
               <p>We live at <placeName id="t17890114-68-crimeloc354">Greenford</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17890114-68-crimeloc354" type="placeName" value="Greenford"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17890114-68-crimeloc354" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17890114-68-off352 t17890114-68-crimeloc354"></join>. My father is a <rs id="t17890114-68-viclabel355" type="occupation">farmer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17890114-68-victim674 t17890114-68-viclabel355"></join>. On the 14th of November, about twelve at night, I heard a noise in the cart-house, which is about forty yards from the house; I got up to the window, and it ceased; then I went to bed again, and I heard a noise of fowls; I told my brother; we went armed to the cart-house, and Guyatt was on a ladder, with a fowl in his hand; we took him, and afterwards we found Carter concealed by a cart; there were three hens and a cock found within a yard of him, dead; I am sure they were my father's. The next morning, we found seven hens, two cocks, two ducks; and a drake, all dead; and a chissel and a bag lying by the side of the hedge secreted.</p>
               <p>
