               <p>I am a brother to the last witness.</p>
               <p>(Deposed to the same effect.)</p>
               <p>PRISONER CARTER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I went into the shed to lie down; I had been looking for some work, and could not get any. I am a sawyer.</p>
               <p>PRISONER GUYATT's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was on the ladder, looking for a little straw to lie down upon.</p>
               <p>BOTH <rs id="t17890114-68-verdict356" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17890114-68-verdict356" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the second Middlesex Jury before the LORD CHIEF BARON.</p>
